<TITLE> Deadline for feedback on education policy stretched to Oct 15 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 30 (bdnews24.com)The government has extended by 15 days the deadline for submission of public recommendations on the proposed national education policy. The feedback can be sent until Oct 15, education minister Nurul Islam Nahim said at a news conference his ministry on Wednesday, when the previous deadline ended. Nahid said, "We got request from people for more time. Also, many people couldn't send their recommendations due to Ramadan and Eid." "We are giving importance to public opinion on it. Considering that, we extended the recommendation submission date up to Oct 15. Hopefully, those who failed to place their opinion until now will be able to do do within the extended time." Storming to power in early January, Awami League formed the National Education Policy Formulation Committee-2009 headed by national professor Kabir Chowdhury. The committee handed over its report to the prime minister on Sep 4 through the education ministry. On the same day, the recommendations made by the committee were published on the education ministry's website seeking public opinion on it. It gave direction to submit recommendations by Sep 30. Nahid said, "The education policy will not be biased to any party. Education policy is not party affairs. That's why everyone's cooperation is needed to implement the education policy." He said the policy will be finalised by this year and implemented from January. Education secretary syed Ataur Rahman was present. bdnews24.
